I believe that, if it hasn't been said already, it's essential that you know you'll always find people who won't necessarily agree with your choices, who won't like your style, your expressions, or whatever else... but never stop believing in yourself, stay the way you are, with your personality and sensitivity that won't be given to everyone, it takes courage! It will allow you to move forward and we can only observe that you fit with any repertoire, I even think your versions are sometimes better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you weren't part of what I would have bet on at first and honestly, I don't remember not appreciating one of your performances, I find you astonishing... to finish, I really enjoyed your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I also liked the original but for once I heard the words clearly, we might have had the impression that you were paying attention not to make any facial expressions, you transmitted emotion to me through my TV so I don't understand why 3 members of the jury didn't feel it! There, I wish you all the best, keep your feet on the ground, don't change anything about what you are, stay humble, stay yourself, make good use of constructive criticism and don't pay attention to those who aren't.
